OL,3,CWeston-super-Mare's former lido one
OL,4,Cstep closer to redevelopment
OL,6,FNorth Somerset Council has progressed
OL,7,Fplans to redevelop Weston-super-Mare's
OL,8,Fformer lido into a 10,000 capacity
OL,9,Fmusic venue.
OL,11,FTropicana opened in 1937 and for a
OL,12,Fwhile it was Europe's largest open-air
OL,13,Fswimming pool. In the first eight
OL,14,Fweeks of it being open, 135,000 people
OL,15,Fvisited the lido.
OL,17,FThe attraction closed in 2000 and for
OL,18,Fdecades since there have been
OL,19,Fquestions asked over what its future
OL,20,Fmay look like.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/5
